description: American English, from Latin ēventu(s)  +‎ -ate, perhaps modeled after actuate.

verbs.description: eventuate (third-person singular simple present eventuates, present participle eventuating, simple past and past participle eventuated)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To have a given result; to turn out (well, badly etc.); to result in. [from 18th c.]
examples: Synonyms: end up, result, turn out

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To happen as a result; to come about. [from 19th c.]
examples: Synonyms: come to pass, occur, transpire; see also Thesaurus:happen
